==English==
===Etymology===
AS. æftan behind; originally superlative of &ldquo;of&rdquo;, off.  See [[After]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /æft/

===Adverb===
{{nautical}} At or towards the [[stern]] of a [[vessel]] (with the frame of reference within the vessel).

===Adjective===
{{nautical}} The corresponding adjective is [[after]], thus "The '''after''' gun is mounted '''aft'''".

===Preposition===
{{nautical}} The corresponding preposition is [[abaft]], thus "The mainmast is '''abaft''' the foremast".

